This is a review paper that puts our work on capillaric circuits in context of microfluidics development in academia and industry over the past three decades. The review was well-received and was featured on the cover of <i>Lab on a Chip</i> because of high scores from reviewers and remains one of the hot articles accessed by readers

[Download paper here](http://academicpages.github.io/files/paper2.pdf)

Recommended citation: Olanrewaju et al. (2018). "Capillary microfluidics in microchannels: from microfluidic networks to capillaric circuits." <i>Lab on a Chip</i>. 18 (16), 2323-2347.
